Review
A journey, initially careless, is complicated because of a series of improper carelessness of a routine journey during the morning shift.
To some extent it was achieved to meet expectations, but this is of no use if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, aroused great expectations already before its debut.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old race saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what he showed, he appears as a game that shouldn't end up being a kind of action again without more.
We were also curious to know how the scenes would stay, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is usually the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much with what we expected.
There are races that can be done for acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
It is not really possible to name mistakes, but rather the incomprehensible misdemeanour of the programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each career takes place through a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant in view, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries in the series.
So it's nothing from the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumnal landscape or the high mountains covered in snow produces a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, careers are sometimes diversified by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance to a required number of rivals (the normal in a classic race), then you try to earn time (the classic timed duel) and then you expect a duel against a single opponent.
In the middle of all this sometimes the police appear, which only makes it difficult even more.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than one could expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the traces of previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be claimed to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race designed with a lot of action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better between the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same no longer occurs with collisions.
Of such games you can't expect it to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or moving the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing out-of-control pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last point of rescue on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just help in case something doesn't go well, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, neither the reset helps, only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, one has to enter a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or five minutes before or after.
This makes anger especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to the meeting in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you get there, you have to turn or stop.
It's the same when you get there, because it's programmed that the "surprise" will always happen in front of your nostrils.
Adversaries also have one more advantage.
During the whole game you will reach places where, regardless of the time, you will always advance the same adversary in the same site.
Moreover, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes before you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come from the front, so at first you can make papillate the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you immediately.
And it's a shame, because even if the travel model is simple, the game is fun and actionable, so it's often not possible to follow the details of what's going on or where.
And it really does the same, if merit is carried the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or classification in the race so that it does not break boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to be careful with the gas pumps next to the road, because right there you have to switch cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, the American strong cars for straight highways and the exotic super-sports for technical driving, for example, on mountain roads with curves.
Also the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know through the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an Online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you reach the subway tunnel (pass), where you run in darkness through the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (step) and, suddenly, the subway convoy arrives behind you and takes you forward without further.
In the wording we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none even thought a bit or whether the authors actually take us for a bunch of bobos.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even proud.
For it is a pity that at the most tense times image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to enjoy most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each one of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final sensation of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoids absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Fun is assured, but prepare because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Academic Festival.
During the same period, there will be twenty corals from high schools and colleges.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"University Carolina has a high stake in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl", said the organization's head, Jakub Čaloun.
The festival's summit is free admission for all audiences to the high school choir concert, to be held on 17 March at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program is attended by Czech jazzist Karel Rąžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening will be held in the places of celebration of the Municipal House in Vynohrady the concert "Students of Terciopelo", in which will participate university corals, including the choir of Uninversity Carolina.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day in dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Tertiple Revolution, but also to present to the public the choral music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebrative concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows of students and morning concerts.
Further information can be found at the festival website www.festaacademica.cz
