Brand story:
The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone were looking for a term that would define IBM's strategy with great precision, the closest would be "long-term".
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has been a hundred years since its foundation.
The basis of this long-term nature was laid by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
