The new leader eclipsed IBM's founder ( Watson's ideas remain the firm foundation on which corporate culture and identity are based).
Watson ran the company until 1952.
IBM, as its name indicates, began with the production and sale of all types of business appliances, from meat and cheese cutters to cash registers.
