How to detect a lie
A look at the most recent headlines tells us how serious and ubiquitous deception and lies are in daily life.
The Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain is busy exchanging accusations of sexual harassment with several women; each side accuses of lying to the other.
The administrators of Pennsylvania State University have been accused of perjury for allegedly concealing reports that said that a retired football coach was sexually assaulting children.
