So it was the work of the cauldron that identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano.
A Californian lobbyist went to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On 4 November, a lobbyist from the Cali CTI went to history as the man who confirmed the identity of the chief of the Farc: "Alfonso Cano", through the coltage of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists working in the sectional of the ITC, that week he played the "availability" shift to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to go to the jungle for more than five days to get to the site where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, he specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, i.e., the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of operation against Alfonso Cano a Eliazar warned him to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big was waiting for you.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being of the man who was leading the world's oldest guerrilla, so they asked him to wear Guillermo León Sáenz's decathyl card (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the body was located, he did not recognize it because of its physical appearance, because it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was without beard, dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body with those of the card.
His eye didn't fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the chief of the FARC.
In search of the footprint
For a dactyloscopicist of Sijín de Cali the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know about our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, with no margin of error, which can become key in the resolution of crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, lobbyists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals have fake ballot papers or have no papers.
We take the fingerprint and look for them in the database.
The investigator reported that, in a case of theft, he was touched by removing a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to pull out a safe full of jewels and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to get a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the impression of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different robberies," he recalled.
The fingerprints may also rule out or reaffirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently they found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
The investigation found that a family member might be a suspect of the crime and, indeed, a mark in the bottle coincided.
Although this doesn't guarantee it was the killer, it does locate it at the scene of the crime.
A CTI dactyloscopicist explained that in the objects "the prints are drawn with chemical or physical reagents".
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," said the ITC expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown in the CSI television program.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that touches becomes a mark.
However, if it can be used, if the respective combination is performed.
